values: I haven't updated in centuries.  Let's see. Ah yes, the highlights of my life.  I have a loving boyfriend, Ross.  This so completely amazing to me since none of my other relationships were real.  This is important, serious, unique.  What can I say...I'm happy.  Perhaps the happiest I have been all year, or all my life.  I know some of you worry about me but right now, I'm in a good place.  I hope to stay in this utopia for a good long while.  I love you all.

Eh sorry for the melodrama of the last entry.  So mom and i spent the day decorating the house with christmas decorations.  It was pretty fun.  When everyone gets back into town ill have to show my fine work.  So i cant wait to see the narnia movie especially since i reread the book.  i think tomorrow ill go and see the aeon flux movie.  it'll give me a chance to get out of the house for a bit.  too bad they dont sell coffee at movie theatres.  hey thats actually a good idea.  maybe ill start my own theatre that does.  hmm. im rambling.  i guess ill go find something to watch on tv. how dull.

Don't grieve for me, for now I'm free
I'm following the path GOd laid for me.
I took His hand when I heard Him call
I turned my back and left it all.

I could not stay another day
To laugh, to love, to work or play.
Tasks left undone must sty that way.
I found that place at the close of day.

If my passing has left a void
Then fill it with remembered joy.
A friendship shared, a laugh, a kiss.
Ah yes, these things, I too, will miss.

Be not burdened with times of sorrow.
I wish you the sunshine of tomorrow.
My life's been full, I savored much
Good friends, good times, a loved one's touch.

Perhaps my time seemed all too brief;
Don't lengthen it now with undue grief.
Lift up your heart and share with me
God wanted me now, He set me free.




This conforts me sometimes.  Other times nothing seems to.  Life seems so meaningless.  I'm fine most days.  Nights are dreadful.  I'm sick of being monitored by my relatives.  I just want to curl up and sleep for centuries.  Don't feel bad for me.  I'm strong. You'll see. I'm strong.
I am home until January 2.  Dear God what am I to do until then?

Even though I dressed up like Alice in Wonderland on Saturday I felt I needed to dress up on Halloween.  Well I zoned out first class today and came up with dressing up as Holly Golightly from Breakfast at Tiffanys.  It worked out so perfectly.  I wish that I could resemble Audrey everyday.  Hope everyone is having an enjoyable holiday.

So I am now back at college.  It's so bizarre to be here again.  My friend and roomie put streamers and balloons in my room.  Also, they got lots of people to put inspirational things on index cards.  So they are covering my walls.  I thought that was pretty sweet.  Thankfully, I was able to finally open my box from my sister.  It contained like a billion presents including a costume of alice in wonderland.  I wore it tonight despite it being in the fourties outside.

Its nice that people are realizing Im back and they are giving me hugs but...I feel so alone now that im not with my family.  I brought some things of my dads so I can remember him but I still feel cut off.  I feel like I will shortly forget my huge tragedy not because I will have gotten over it but because there is so much other junk to preoccupy me.  

Most days I am pretty stable (visibly speaking).  At the most random times, I'll remember some memory concerning my dad and it will make me cry.  Noone really notices when this happens and the sadness soon passes.  I guess this is what they meant when they said the pain wont go away but lessen in time.  

I feel like jumping off the bluffs everytime I think of the homework I have to catch up on.  Its now more important than ever that I get good grades because I need the scholarship.  Living takes so much strength and I feel weak.

This must be the longest post Ive written in some time.  I guess I'll sleep or find where everyone is hiding.  Thanks to all who have me in their prayers.

Thanks to everyone for their comments.  You don't know how much it means to me that there are so many people who care.  The family is holding it together.  Luckily, all the cops that worked with my dad have helped us so much.  They take us to the airport, bring food, help make arrangements.  I dont know what my mom would have done without all that support.  I know my dad is somewhere good and that gives me peace.  I still cant believe that my heroic indestructible dad was indeed destructible. naivity sucks ass.

I have been meaning to write for a while.  I feel the need to tell everyone what im going through at the moment.  Yesterday, October 22, my mother told me that my dad was in a motorcycle accident resulting in his death.  I flew home last night and I will continue to be here all week.  I confess it has not sunk in and I dont know if it ever will.  I am numb.  God bless his soul.

Wow. So CJ hasn't updated in forever.  I can't believe its midterms already.  Oh I must thank all who have written to me.  I cannot express the joyous sensation of opening my mailbox and finding a letter there.  I have not as of yet found the time to return the favor but i assure you all that I will get to it eventually.  
Hmm well nothing too exciting here.  I actually missed class the other day because I was "in". This means that I was sick and slept in. haha.  I feel much better now though.  Oh funny, it seems everyone knows that tuesday is my night with the big tv to watch gilmore girls.  AND I know a guy named paul that i totally call paul anka, hahaha. he doesnt like it much.
Well I am sure there is much much more I could say but I've had a long day and I must wake up at 7 so tah tah my loves!

ps: my co-conspirators rock, aka Cecily and Bronwen

I feel it has been far too long since my last entry.  For all of you who wanted to know, my addy is: Christi Green
    Principia College #49
    1 Maybeck Place
    Elsah, IL 62028

So I have finally started classes.  It feels so good to get into the swing of things.  My first class is called people of courage.  I really love me teacher because he is this lil old british man who gets so super excited when teaching.  Corresponging with that course, I am taking...ASTRONOMY!!! I love it.  I am so happy to be taking that class.  The teacher is also my advisor.  Finally, I am taking Chem.  So are all science teachers a lil crazy? Yeah I think so.

So my social life you ask. haha haha hahah.  Well I have tons of guys friends.  I find it easier that way because guys arent as high maintanence as girls.  I have been not obsessing about the guys I posted about earlier.  It could just be my overactive imagination but I think he is paying more attention to me now.  Who knows? Who cares?  There is another guy here that I took pity on because my friend dumped him harshly.  I thought that he was fairly attractive (and Canadian) so I kinda flirted with him.  One night during a movie, he held and played with my hand.  Perfect right?

HELL NO

Turns out he has been "playin" a lot of girls.  I do not like being on someones LIST!  Anyway we had a long talk and now it is my job to tell him when hes being a cocky asshole.  basically all the freakin time.  So for now there is no interest there romantically but I do like the fact that he can confide in me.

Well I better go seeing as I have to read 47 more pages on Mandela. Night to everyone. I miss you all so much.  I talk about ya'll all the time.  You're in my heart.

Sorry it has taken so long for this update to be written.  I can hardly believe I have been in college for only a week.  It feels like I have been here so long already.  I met a lot of interesting people here.  Muchos chicos guapos. mmm.  I register for classes tomorrow.  I am taking a course called people of courage along with an astronomy and chemisty class this quarter.  I am really excited about starting actual classes and upper classmen move in on friday.  
    My friend Tiffany and I started a new task here.  We go around to all the guys dorms we know and leave them postit messages on their doors.  They seem to really like it.  I love to make a difference in people's days.  I am going to continue doing this in the weeks to come.  It also gives me a chance to go by my crushes room.
    Yes, I know. Crush already.  Well listen...he is a musician who plays guitar, bass, and drums.  He is funny, cute, with beautiful blue eyes.  The only problem is that he has known a girl here since like he was ten from camp.  He seems to like her a lot but I don't think she likes him in that way.  All the same, he flirts with me sometimes so I won't give up yet.  I don't have it in me too.  I am trying to just treat him like a friend and let the rest just fade away.
    I'm sure there is plenty more that I could write but the others are watching a movie (surprise, surprise).  I promise to update again soon. love ya'll. ps. Im trying to get everyone to start saying ya'll, lol!

This is officially my last update.  I still have some things to pack and its almost 11.  I will miss you all.  I will probably get online in the morning right before I leave around 8 but I doubt anyone else will be on.  Good luck to you all.  Thanks for all the memories.

"Good Riddance (Time Of Your Life)"

Another turning point, a fork stuck in the road
Time grabs you by the wrist, directs you where to go
So make the best of this test, and don't ask why
It's not a question, but a lesson learned in time

It's something unpredictable, but in the end it's right.
I hope you had the time of your life.

Well today I got down to business and really started packing.  I realized something...I have too much clothes/shoes.  Its really ridiculous.  I dont know how Ill pack it all.  Actually my mother is an awesome packer so im getting her assistance tonight.  

In other news, I treated myself to a starbucks run today.  I could not have left for college without having my last caramel mach. Heck I might go back tomorrow.  The cute guy with the glasses was there.  He kept asking me if I wanted to try any food.  I only go there for the drinks and guys.  I brought my book on the history of phi so as to make me seem intelligent (plus I really like this book).  There were a group of men having a business meeting there.  It was so bizarre.  I did start listening when they were talking about their demographic and such and what models they wanted to use.  They kinda pissed me off a lil. "Oh we're going for the cheerleading crowd not those boring girls."  AHHHH.  You are all boring, old, creepy men.

Tomorrow my dad is taking off work to help me finish packing.  Oh ya'll who have started classes have given me hope.  You all seem to think the work is easy so Im going to stop stressing so much.  I will try my hardest to update on Friday.  Maybe my roommate will have a computer she doesnt mind sharing.  

Well, thats all thats on my mind. Oh Im going to start saying these thing (from my book):

     As soon as you awake, in order lay
     the actions to be done the coming day.

     Allow not sleep to close your eyes
     before three times reflecting on
     your actions of the day.  What deeds
     done well, what not, what left undone?

I'm back finally.  It is hard believe I only have about another week before I'm gone for good.  Call me if you want to hang. I'm up for anything.

Well, I'm off...again.  Travel seems to be what I do best.  Too bad I didn't get to say goodbye to anyone in person.  Oh just to be clear. I am not going to college yet, just a trip with my family up north.  I decided that I would reread the fifth hp book on the way up (we are driving).  I doubt I will have any computer access for the next ten days but if you're lucky I'll call or send a postcard.  Everyone stay out of trouble.  Miss me because I will miss all of you.  Adieux!

I am now going to be an aunt!  My sister just called this morning with the news.  I am soooo happy for her.  Luckily she is getting leave around the time the baby comes so we can see her.  OHHH I can not wait to buy lil baby things.  This news seriously makes my day. :)

This has been the most pointless day ever.  I have accomplished absolutely nothing at all.  I wish I could have done something with my friends because we only have a short time left but they all seemed to be busy.  Maybe this is a sign that I should have gone to OK.  I mean I thought long and hard about it but it just doesn't seem like me to chase down a guy I dont know.  I will probably regret but whatever.  

Hmm its 8:30 so if anyone reads this and wants to do something tonight im up for it.

I changed my icon.  Other than that I've just been doing lots of laundry.  It's not fun.  At least it is easy and I have had lots of practice through the years.  

I need rest.

Well I got to see my sister and bro in law one last time before they left for Japan.  I think I'll really miss them.  I hope I can save up money so I can visit them during next summer.  That would be an amazing travel experience.  
     Im particularly happy at the moment due to the fact that I just consumed a grande iced white choc mocha. mmmm.  I've been thinking about college a lot today.  I have to decide on this thing call first year experience.  I have nine choices of classes to take for it.  I can't decide at all.  I think I might go for the People of Courage (HIST) and Descriptive Astronomy (PHYS) route.  They are described as the most challenging but they are also the most interesting.  I'd rather not go the Chemistry route...hahahaha.  I think im going to stay pretty focused on college stuff.  I dont want to be tied down at all this summer.  Sometime today or tomorrow im going to sit down and consider everything im interested in and plan on what to major in.  I hate not having a plan.  I feel unfocused.  A drifter.

So I have a brother in law now.  It hasn't really sunken in yet.  I thought the wedding was lovely.  I'm glad that Sara and Katie showed up even though they sat by themselves.  I was trying to set them up with the two ushers but that didn't work very well.  Now everyone has left except my Aunt.  I'm pretty tired.  I did get my much needed starbucks today though. hehe.  I believe we are all going to see the Interpreter.  I'm sorry this all seems very disjointed.  I attribute it to my lethargic state of mind.  That's all for now.  Oh and I'm pretty much free from now on so leave me a message if you want to do anything.  At the very least, come over and help eat the remaining wedding cake.;)

My dad actually had the night off tonight.  It was so bizarre.  I promptly dropped all the plans I had for this evening and went out to eat with him.  We stopped at the phone store first and finally had my voicemail fixed.  I was especially grateful of this considering it hasn't worked for the past two months.  A few of the guys there apparently knew my dad quite well and told me I was lucky to be his daughter.  I hear that a lot actually. It's an ironic statement really, he seems to be there in everyones lives but mine.  So we went to eat.  I just started talking to my dad about everything and anything I could think of at the time.  I mean we hadn't had a real conversation in weeks.  It was nice to talk but at the same time it seemed he was not listening to what I was saying.  He had a margarita to "relax himself".  I think he depends too much on them and I think he should quit drinking completely.  I guess tonight was bittersweet but I am still appreciative of being in the same room with my dad for once.

Sorry guys, i don't have much to say.  This day really put me in a bad mood. Most of ya'll heard my story about this morning which im still not over.  This afternoon i burnt the roof of my mouth.  It really hurts badly...i mean badly...plus i have a molar that finally coming in...ouch.  So besides all that complaining, i dont have anything to say.  Sorry guys, i hate complainers...so just forget everything you just read.

I was thinking about life today.  I mean I was seriously thinking about it.  I was never one of those kids with a plan for life.  I fear I never will.  There are a few things I do know I want.  I want to be successful, make a positive impact on the world, have a marriage that works if that is possible, and have lovely children.  I'm not even sure if I can accomplish these things. My mom seems to think I am not the marrying type.  What are the odds of finding the right guy.  Will I mess it up if I meet him?  hmm.  Well I was also thinking about how cut off I will feel in college away from the friends I love.  We all say that we will keep in touch but that just isnt realistic in the least.  I don't even know if I will have the internet.  Bottom line: My life is a changing and I fight change.
coldness surrounds me. both literally and figuratively.
